data.title: iDKHOW to Headline Fork Fest 2021
data.meta_description: Fork Fest 2021 will kickoff the summer with a surprise headliner, twenty-eight bands, three stages, and a large selection of food trucks, artists, and vendors.
data.text:
By Zach Collier

The lineup for Fork Fest 2021 was just announced, and the news is making waves. I DONT KNOW HOW BUT THEY FOUND ME will be headlining this yearsâ€™ festival. The Salt Lake City based duo consists of lead vocalist and bassist Dallon Weekes and drummer Ryan Seaman. Weekes is known for his work with the power pop band The Brobecks and most notably as the touring bassist for Panic! at the Disco.

Other notable acts taking the stage this year are Fictionist, Sego, Mindy Gledhill, and Book On Tape Worm. Fork Fest 2021 will kickoff the summer with twenty-eight bands, three stages, and a large selection of food trucks, artists, and vendors.

Presented by The Harrington Center for the Arts and Velour Live Music Gallery, Fork Fest will take place June 19th, 2021. General Admission is $25. VIP Tickets are $45. Tickets are available online here. You can check out the full lineup below.
